<section xml:id="data-types-and-entering-data-for-test-cases" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                                        xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                                        xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Data types and entering data for Test Cases</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerPropertiesViewContextId" xml:id="data-types-and-entering-data-for-test-cases.guidancerPropertiesViewContextId" xreflabel="Properties View"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId" xml:id="data-types-and-entering-data-for-test-cases.guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId" xreflabel="Test Case Editor"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerDataSetViewContextId" xml:id="data-types-and-entering-data-for-test-cases.guidancerDataSetViewContextId" xreflabel="Data Sets View"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerCentralTestDataEditorContextId" xml:id="data-types-and-entering-data-for-test-cases.guidancerCentralTestDataEditorContextId" xreflabel="Central Test Data"/>
  <para>
    Most actions in the library require one or more
    <emphasis>parameters</emphasis> (e.g. how often to click, what
    text to enter). Once you have added Test Cases or Test Steps to
    a Test Case, you will see which parameters are required by this
    action in the Properties View.
  </para>
  <para role="tip">
    You can also enter <emphasis>data sets</emphasis> in the
    Data Sets View (<xref linkend="using-the-data-sets-view"/>) and you can create
    central data sets to be reused throughout the Project
    (<xref linkend="using-central-data-sets"/>).
  </para>
  <para>
    You can be very flexible with data, so you have a choice about
    what to enter in the Properties View:
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Concrete values (<xref linkend="entering-concrete-values-as-data-in-test-cases"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        References (<xref linkend="using-references-for-data-in-test-cases"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Variables (<xref linkend="using-variables-as-data-for-test-cases"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Functions (<xref linkend="using-functions-as-data-for-test-cases"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        A mixture of the above (<xref linkend="concatenating-combining-parameters"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        An Excel file (<xref linkend="using-an-excel-file-as-an-external-data-source"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        A reference to a central data set (<xref linkend="using-central-data-sets"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>